idCitation.resTitle: BOEM Marine Hydrokinetic Leases and Planning Areas

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Active research or commercial marine hydrokinetic leases or areas being considered for future leasing (planning areas).
dataIdInfo.idCredit:
Public information, no credit necessary.
Compiler is Josh Wadlington - Bureau of Ocean Energy Management. Additional collaborators are Christine Taylor and Frank Pendleton - Bureau of Ocean Energy Management.

Consts.useLimit:
Not for navigational use. Not to be used for leasing purposes. For visual purposes only.

February 16, 2021 – BOEM Issues Lease to Oregon State University for the PacWave South Project, the First Wave Energy Research Project in Federal Waters Offshore the U.S. West Coast.

January 19, 2021 – BOEM issued a Finding of No Significant Impact and offered a Marine Hydrokinetic Research Lease to Oregon State University for the PacWave South Project

ConResult.conExpl: This dataset is believed to be free from errors, however inconsistencies are possible.

dataLineage.statement: This dataset is subject to periodic revision and represents only the most recent version of the features displayed. Archival data about the history of the leasing areas is maintained by the Bureau of Ocean Energy Management, however it is not included in this dataset.
